# Credit Risk & Receivables Dashboard — Cursor build rules
#
# Source of truth for detail: docs/business_requirements.md
# This file is a condensed reference for incremental implementation.

## Stack (locked)
Python 3.11+, Streamlit, pandas, numpy, Plotly, DuckDB, PyArrow, Faker,
Pydantic, PyYAML, pytest, Ruff, Docker. No Power BI / DAX / proprietary BI.

Prefer standard Streamlit over optional libs (aggrid, option-menu, GE, etc.)
unless a clear gap appears.

## Architecture
- Pipeline (`src/`) generates synthetic data, validates, scores risk, writes
  DuckDB + Parquet. Streamlit only reads analytical tables.
- Navigation: native multipage — `app/Home.py` + `app/pages/01_…`–`05_…`.
- Shared filters: `app/components/filters.py` → `st.session_state`.
- SQL lives in `sql/`; pages call `app/services/` only — no inline SQL in pages.
- Caching: `st.cache_resource` for DB; `st.cache_data(ttl=…)` for queries,
  keyed by refresh timestamp after pipeline runs.

## Config
Validate `config/project_config.yaml` via Pydantic (`src/config.py`) before use.
Dashboard / database / application sections are required.

## Demo disclaimer (keep visible on Home and wherever risk scores appear)
> This application uses a fictional dataset and a demonstration risk
> methodology. It is not a production credit-rating model, regulatory model,
> or substitute for professional underwriting judgement.

## Current phase
Phases 1–2 complete. Next: Phase 3 (risk analytics / collections priority).
See business_requirements.md §27 and docs/phase2_plan.md (historical).

## Working style
- Implement one phase at a time (see business_requirements.md §27).
- After each phase: list changed files, run relevant tests /
  `python -m src.run_pipeline --small`, smoke-test the app when applicable.
- Fix failures before starting the next phase.
- Missing DuckDB → friendly “run the pipeline” message, never an unhandled crash.
- User-friendly errors; log technical detail; no bare `except`.

## Styling (§20–21)
Dark navy headings, neutral background, blue for neutral values, amber warnings,
red critical, green favourable. Theme in `.streamlit/config.toml`; limited CSS.
Never commit `.streamlit/secrets.toml` — placeholders only in `secrets.toml.example`.

## Do not
- Scatter SQL through page modules.
- Recompute risk / collections scores inside Streamlit render.
- Depend on Power BI or closed-source BI tooling.
- Hide core Streamlit controls with fragile CSS.
